nerations of scholars, and how his journey led him from crisis theology to the Frankfurt School, and from a radical Hasidic sect in Jerusalem to the center of academic debates over Gnosticism, secularization, and the revolutionary potential of apocalypticism.Professor of Apocalypse offers an unforgettable account of an electrifying world of ideas, focused on a charismatic personality who thrived on controversy and conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJewish philosopherszGermanyvBiography. 0aJewish philosopherszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aPhilosophyxHistoryy20th century. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Philosophers.2bisacsh  aAlain Badiou.  aAntithesis.  aAppeasement.  aAptitude.  aAwareness.  aBaal Shem Tov.  aBiblical canon.  aBoarding school.  aCalvinism.  aCarl Schmitt.  aCatechism.  aCheese sandwich.  aChristianity.  aConsciousness.  aControversy.  aCorrespondent.  aCosmopolitanism.  aCritique.  aDepartment store.  aDieter Henrich.  aDissident.  aErnst Bloch.  aFatah.  aFaust.  aFirst language.  aGeorg Wilhelm Friedrich Hegel.  aGerman resistance to Nazism.  aGiorgio Agamben.  aGnosticism.  aGolden calf.  aGraduation.  aHabilitation.  aHans Heinz Holz.  aHerbert Marcuse.  aHermeneutics.  aHuman science.  aI Wish (manhwa).  aIdiosyncrasy.  aImplementation.  aIngredient.  aInstitution.  aIranian studies.  aItalians.  aJacob Taubes.  aJews.  aJudaism.  aLate capitalism.  aLaughter.  aLecture.  aLeo Strauss.  aLionel Trilling.  aMaimonides.  aMartin Buber.  aMartin Heidegger.  aMarxism.  aMemoir.  aMilitary alliance.  aMiracle.  aNachman Krochmal.  aNathan Glazer.  aNazi Germany.  aOpen letter.  aOral sex.  aPamphlet.  aPeter Sloterdijk.  aPhilosopher.  aPhilosophy.  aPie